field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Folk5 is 10 nm Ir on 5 nm Ti on Au, sputtered earlier this week, Reshma1B is 25nm RuO2 sputtered at RT on 5nm Ti on GC. Rao1D is 10 ug hydrous RuO2 nanoparticles
field_data.Removed from vacuum: Folk5 and Reshma1B had I.S.S. done, just came out of Omicron. Rao1D has been in air since last time.

notes: 01... Clear isotope exchange on Folk5! :D ... but it's the first in 16O after a lot in 18O, so some doubt, link 1 below. ISS will say for sure. Noise in CV's due to Al-rusty CE wire. Then, huge shunt current also offseting potential on some of WE as evidenced by O2 evolution. No fun. Remounting and restarting. 02... M34/M32 ratio seems basically to continue from where left off, a good sign that this is indeed exchange. link 1: https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=200&xmax=1000&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_ymin=0&left_ymax=3.8e-10&right_ymin=1.45e-12&right_ymax=3.5e-12&left_plotlist%5B%5D=13009&right_plotlist%5B%5D=13010&chosen_group%5B%5D=2018-09-18+20%3A39%3A47 ------ Rreshma1B ------ 01... everything functioning perfectly. Also a quantifiable amount of exchange here! Link 2, below. But much less than Folk5. This is beautiful. m/z=46 to m/z=44 ratio much higher than I can explain, but constant. Lack of transient m/z=46 is in contrast to the transient m/z=44 when doing this in 18O. This points towards adsorbed CO2 from air. Also, Reshma1B matches itself in 18O from earlier today so perectly that I feel fine without an additional RHE cal. link 2: https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=200&xmax=1500&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_ymin=0&left_ymax=0&right_ymin=0&right_ymax=0&left_plotlist%5B%5D=13009&right_plotlist%5B%5D=13010&chosen_group%5B%5D=2018-09-18+20%3A39%3A47 ---- Rao1D ----- Again, quantifiable :) but very small isotope effect. Looking back, Rao1F was NOT OXIDIZED when I finished its experiment on sunday. That was STUPID! I will have to do it again, but not now. This is my last thing. Activity and capacitance both appear lower than before. Not really any point in continuing the measurement. ----- Trimi1 ------- Final calibration before I go home and go to the USA. It actually looks more like RE_vs_RHE=0.715
